Earl Basil TUCKER v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5756. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. March 11, 1958. Donald E. Kelley, U. S. Atty., and Robert S. Wham, Asst. U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and HUXMAN and MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute the same.
